Title: Diagnosis of test `test_pct_change_with_duplicate_axis`

Details: 
The test `test_pct_change_with_duplicate_axis` aims to validate the behavior of the `pct_change` method of the `Series` class when the index contains duplicate values. The test encounters an error because the method `pct_change` internally calls the `reindex` method, which does not handle duplicate indices properly.

The error traceback indicates that the failure point lies in the `reindex_like` method called within `pct_change`, leading to `_reindex_with_indexers`, and eventually hitting `_can_reindex` in the `BlockManager`. The key function `_can_reindex` raises the `ValueError` when it detects duplicate values in the index:

```python
pandas/core/internals/managers.py:
1240: self.axes[axis]._can_reindex(indexer)
1241: if not allow_dups:
1242:     self.axes[axis]._can_reindex(indexer)
```

Since `allow_dups` is set to `False` by default, the presence of duplicate indices causes the method to raise an error.

To resolve this, modifications are needed in the `Series.pct_change` implementation to handle cases with duplicate indices appropriately.

The following methods are most likely the best locations for the fix:

1. `pandas.core.series.Series.pct_change`
2. `pandas.core.generic.NDFrame.reindex`

Based on the available information, provide the signatures of the most likely culprit methods for the bug. Your answer will be processed automatically, so make sure to only answer with the accurate signatures of all likely culprits (in `ClassName.MethodName(ArgType1, ArgType2, ...)` format), without commentary (one per line).

Title: Diagnosis of test `test_pct_change_with_duplicate_axis`

Details: 
The test `test_pct_change_with_duplicate_axis` aims to validate the behavior of the `pct_change` method of the `Series` class when the index contains duplicate values. The test encounters an error because the method `pct_change` internally calls the `reindex` method, which does not handle duplicate indices properly.

The error traceback indicates that the failure point lies in the `reindex_like` method called within `pct_change`, leading to `_reindex_with_indexers`, and eventually hitting `_can_reindex` in the `BlockManager`. The key function `_can_reindex` raises the `ValueError` when it detects duplicate values in the index:

```python
pandas/core/internals/managers.py:
1240: self.axes[axis]._can_reindex(indexer)
1241: if not allow_dups:
1242:     self.axes[axis]._can_reindex(indexer)
```

Since `allow_dups` is set to `False` by default, the presence of duplicate indices causes the method to raise an error.

To resolve this, modifications are needed in the `Series.pct_change` implementation to handle cases with duplicate indices appropriately.

The following methods are most likely the best locations for the fix:

1. `pandas.core.series.Series.pct_change`
2. `pandas.core.generic.NDFrame.reindex`
